CGP Ep472 Expectations (link in bio) 📡
The only thing you can be certain of in life is that life is uncertain. To have expectations means that you expect the world to colour inside the lines you drew. Expectations take us out of the now and into the uncertain future with the belief that it will turn out the way we expect it to. You need to clear and solid foundation of beliefs and rules that you live YOUR life by. You can't expect the rest of the world to follow these tenets. Doing so, will leave you disappointed. @mytpi @perform_better

Many different ways to load the backswing. This drill focussed on stability, awareness and control at the top of the backswing. The cable is pulling the athlete into reverse spine, loss of posture and over rotation. The athlete has to control the load and resist these characteristics. Simple but extremely effective in creating awareness. Next step? Let them feel too much rotation (long drive) too little (@jonrahm feel) and then “just right” Where do you feel the load? @mytpi @golfforeverprogram #loadXplode #thecompound

CGP Ep494 Eccentric Elastic Loads
I experiment in my gym each week with different ways to load the body in an attempt to make it Xplode! Add a load to the body and the body will adapt to that load. But no all loads are created equal! You have different ways for the body to handle the load. Different types of contractions to manage the loads. Concentric (yawn), Isometric (double yawn) and most exciting, Eccentric (Gahhdouche). Eccentric contractions are where the muscle is actively lengthening. Think about slowly lowering a mountain climber on a rope. The rope is getting longer but it is always under tension.  This illicit incredible adaptation in the muscle fibers. This makes you LoadXplode faster. Want to hear some of my favourite Eccentric exercises? Wanna hear how I add elastic components to the eccentric training? Hmmm.....well....do you? Well listen up Sonny Boy! 👉 Podcast in Bio @forwellness @mytpi @perform_better @superspeedgolf

We are very excited to be working with Jason Glass as one of our new SuperSpeed Ambassadors. Jason is the head of the @mytpi fitness advisory board and has been on the cutting edge of rotational power training for his entire career. 

As one of the world’s top Golf Strength & Conditioning Specialists, Jason is frequently out on the PGA Tour training many of the best players. 

In partnership with Jason, we're gong to be launching 3 new strength protocols, a mobility protocol, and an advanced speed activation protocol. These protocols are specifically designed to support our SuperSpeed Golf Training programs. Stay tuned for more information coming soon and release dates!

I've worked with the SuperSpeed Training system for many years and seen how it has helped many players increase swing speed. I'm really pumped to be part of the fold with the SuperSpeed Team. I think it is going to make a great thing even better. - Jason

DreamBIG Feb 24th, 2014: I want the Coach Glass Podcast to get to 500 episodes and have over 1 Million Glistener downloads. Crazy dream, but we were able to OverDelivered on it. I have goosebumps right now at the thought of it. I remember it like it was yesterday. My guts were churning as I pressed "publish" and sent the first episode into the etherwebs! CGP Ep1 Start of Something BIG was a hit. I had no idea how far it would take me and the wild ride it would be. So many great guests, touching stories, inspirational moments and way too many sound effects. In this epic episode we go DEEEP into the highlights from the past 9 years of podcasting. I want to thank all my Glisteners for making this possible. You kept me turning on the mic week after week, fuelled by your kind emails and social media shares. I am honoured to be your Coach! What's next for the Coach Glass Podcast? You will have to listen to find out!!!!

⚠️ NEW PODCAST EP ⏯️ LINK IN BIO 🆗 The King of OverDeliver is telling you to DO LESS. Do less in your workouts, do les in your career, do less in your relationships, do less in your life and you will get MORE! I am not talking about being lazy. Ohhh no far from it. I want you to do less but deliver more. More quality, more depth, more of you! You are enough just the way you are. Watch what happens when you try less and allow the real you to be truly seen.  Powerful stuff folks. Just listen. @mytpi @perform_better @superspeedgolf
